you could us an abacus, you could anzan, you

00:37:01.002 --> 00:37:04.720
could do all these things, so it's not good,
that task just saying something.

00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:11.800
And then he had this idea, "Why don't I have
a computer screen flashing digits so fast

00:37:11.800 --> 00:37:17.950
that you can't write them down and work out
a task like that?" So he invented this game

00:37:17.950 --> 00:37:23.000
called Flash Anzan which I'm gonna show you
now which flashes digits incredibly fast and

00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:27.540
the idea is in this game here particularly
to add them all up. So what you're gonna see

00:37:27.540 --> 00:37:35.040
is 15 digits and they're all three number
digits, three digit numbers, so like 221 is

00:37:35.040 --> 00:37:39.650
a three digit number, 15 of them in three
seconds, that's five per second and the purpose

00:37:39.650 --> 00:37:53.660
or the object is to count them and say the
answer, to add them all up.

00:37:53.660 --> 00:37:54.940
[pause]

